entries.description: Dark blue brand color (45% lightness). Adjusted to maintain consistent ramp progression.
Purple brand color (50% lightness). Adjusted to maintain consistent ramp progression.
Base spacing unit (2px). All spacing scales are multiples of this value. Figma variable type: SPACING.
010 spacing (2px). Use for micro spacing needs.
020 spacing (4px). Use for tight spacing between small elements.
030 spacing (8px). Use for padding inside compact components.
040 spacing (16px). Use for default padding and margins.
050 spacing (24px). Use for section padding and larger margins.
060 spacing (32px). Use for major section spacing.
070 spacing (40px). Use for large vertical rhythm.
080 spacing (48px). Use for major vertical spacing.
090 spacing (64px). Use for hero section spacing.
100 spacing (80px). Use for large hero spacing.
110 spacing (96px). Use for extra large spacing.
Active border - default state. Black border for selected elements.
Primary button background - default state. References brand pink (#da095e).
Primary button icon - default state. References primary text color.
Primary button text - default state. White text on pink background.
Border for elevated surfaces (cards, modals, popovers) to enhance depth perception. Use with surface elevation levels 1-4.
Border on top of accent-colored surfaces. Use for badges, labels, or containers on accent backgrounds.
Primary border for UI separation and container outlines. Use for card borders, section dividers, and strong visual separation. (35% lightness)
Secondary border for nested containers or less important separation. Use for nested cards, form field groups, and subtle dividers. (40% lightness)
Tertiary border for minimal visual distinction. Use for grid lines and subtle separators in dense interfaces. (45% lightness)
Disabled state palette option A. Light grey (89% lightness) for flexible component combinations. Use with disabled.b and/or disabled.c based on component aesthetics.
Disabled state palette option B. Light-mid grey (79% lightness) for contrast and emphasis. Use with disabled.a and/or disabled.c based on component aesthetics.
Disabled state palette option C. Mid grey (69% lightness) for critical text/borders. Use with disabled.a and/or disabled.b based on component aesthetics.
Error banner/alert border. Emphasizes error state visually. Same as text color for cohesion.
Error banner/alert background. Use for error state containers. Light red tint for visibility.
Error banner/alert icon color. Matches text and border for visual consistency.
Error banner/alert text and headings. High contrast dark red for readability on light backgrounds.
Info banner/alert border. Emphasizes info state visually. Same as text color for cohesion.
Info banner/alert background. Use for informational containers. Light blue tint for visibility.
Info banner/alert icon color. Matches text and border for visual consistency.
Info banner/alert text and headings. High contrast dark blue for readability on light backgrounds.
Success banner/alert border. Emphasizes success state visually. Same as text color for cohesion.
Success banner/alert background. Use for success/confirmation containers. Light green tint for visibility.
Success banner/alert icon color. Matches text and border for visual consistency.
Success banner/alert text and headings. High contrast dark green for readability on light backgrounds.
Warning banner/alert border. Emphasizes warning state visually. Uses darker orange for strong emphasis.
Warning banner/alert background. Use for warning/caution containers. Light yellow tint for visibility.
Warning banner/alert icon color. Matches text and border for visual consistency.
Warning banner/alert text and headings. High contrast dark orange for readability on light backgrounds.
Focus border color for keyboard navigation. Uses dark blue ramp for high contrast (4.5:1 on white).
Border color for input fields when active (pressed) or focused. Uses brand pink for clear visual indication.
Border color for input fields in their standard state.
Border color for input fields in an error validation state.
Border color for input fields when hovered by the user.
Border color for input fields in a success validation state.
Background for input fields when active (pressed) or focused.
Default background for input fields in their standard state.
Background for input fields in an error validation state.
Background for input fields when hovered by the user.
Background for input fields in a success validation state.
Icon color for input fields when active (pressed) or focused. References input.text.active for consistency.
Icon color for input fields in an error validation state. References input.text.error for consistency.
Icon color for input fields when hovered by the user. References input.text.hover for consistency.
Placeholder icon color for input fields. References input.text.placeholder for consistency.
Icon color for input fields in a success validation state. References input.text.success for consistency.
Text color for input fields when active (pressed) or focused.
Text color for input fields in an error validation state.
Text color for input fields when hovered by the user.
Placeholder text color for input fields.
Text color for input fields in a success validation state.
Link color - default state. Use for hyperlinks and text links. Purple for recognizable link appearance.
Link color - hover state. Darker purple for visual feedback.
Link color - visited state. Darker purple to indicate visited links.
Primary button background - default state. References brand pink (#da095e).
Primary button background - hover state. 41% lightness, WCAG White AA Normal.
Primary button background - pressed state. 32% lightness, WCAG White AAA Normal.
Primary button icon - default state. References primary text color.
Primary button icon - hover state. References primary text hover color.
Primary button icon - pressed state. References primary text pressed color.
Primary button text - default state. White text on pink background.
Primary button text - hover state. 85% lightness for subtle contrast reduction.
Primary button text - pressed state. 75% lightness for visual feedback.
Secondary button border - default state. References brand purple (#8b006e).
Secondary button border - hover state. 41% lightness, darker purple for emphasis.
Secondary button border - pressed state. 32% lightness, darkest purple for pressed state.
Secondary button background - default state. White background.
Secondary button background - hover state. 85% lightness for subtle hover effect.
Secondary button background - pressed state. 75% lightness for pressed feedback.
Secondary button icon - default state. References secondary text color.
Secondary button icon - hover state. References secondary text hover color.
Secondary button icon - pressed state. References secondary text pressed color.
Secondary button text - all states. Black text on white/light backgrounds.
Secondary button text - hover state. Consistent black text.
Secondary button text - pressed state. Consistent black text.
High intensity accent color for surface (approx 62.5% lightness). Use for strong highlights or badges.
Low intensity accent color for surface (approx 82.5% lightness). Use for subtle highlights or backgrounds.
Medium intensity accent color for surface (approx 67.5% lightness). Use for moderate highlights.
Canvas background fill (elevation level 0). Use as primary page/screen background. Base surface for all UI elements.
Inverse surface fill (dark background). Use for dark mode or high-contrast sections. Provides visual separation.
Level 1 surface fill (elevation level 1). Use for cards and contained components. Creates first tier of elevation.
Level 2 surface fill (elevation level 2). Use for overlays, popovers, tooltips. Creates second tier of elevation.
Level 3 surface fill (elevation level 3). Use for modals and prominent overlays. Creates third tier of elevation.
Level 4 surface fill (elevation level 4). Use for top-level modals and dropdowns. Creates fourth tier of elevation.
Undercanvas background fill (elevation level -1). Use for elements below the main canvas. Provides subtle depth perception.
Body Large: 18px, Regular weight. For lead paragraphs and prominent body text.
Body Medium: 16px, Regular weight. Standard body text.
Body Small: 14px, Regular weight. Secondary body text.
Caption Medium: Explanatory text. Scales from 10px (small) to 14px (xlarge).
Caption Small: Micro text/labels. Scales from 8px (small) to 10px (xlarge).
Headline Large: High impact heading. Scales from 28px (small) to 40px (xlarge).
Headline Medium: Standard page heading. Scales from 24px (small) to 34px (xlarge).
Headline Small: Section heading. Scales from 20px (small) to 28px (xlarge).
Label Large: 18px, Bold weight. For prominent form labels and UI labels.
Label Medium: 16px, Bold weight. Standard form labels and UI labels.
Label Small: 14px, Bold weight. Compact form labels and UI labels.
Link Large: 18px, Regular weight, underline. Aligns with body large text.
Link Medium: 16px, Regular weight, underline. Aligns with body medium text.
Link Small: 14px, Regular weight, underline. Aligns with body small text.
Link Small: 14px, Regular weight, underline. Aligns with body small text.
Canvas shadow. Minimal shadow for subtle definition on canvas level.
Level 1 shadow. Noticeable elevation for cards and floating elements.
Level 2 shadow. Stronger elevation for dropdowns and popovers.
Level 3 shadow. Pronounced elevation for sticky headers and persistent UI.
Level 4 shadow. Maximum elevation for modals and top-level overlays.
Inverse shadow. Light shadow on dark backgrounds for high contrast.
Undercanvas shadow. No visible shadow (elevation below canvas).
Subheadline Large: Prominent subsection title. Scales from 20px (small) to 26px (xlarge).
Subheadline Medium: Standard subsection title. Scales from 18px (small) to 24px (xlarge).
Subheadline Small: Minor subsection title. Scales from 16px (small) to 22px (xlarge).
